n Switerland to the inauguration of the railway line. Subsequently, it describes how the railway line was portrayed in travel guides of the belle poque. The last chapter captures the glory days of the Gotthard myth, before and during the Second World War, with a focus on novels and plays in which the Gotthard Tunnel construction occurs. This historical overview offers insight into the multiple roles that technology plays in the construction of a sense of national identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aHistory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013z978311070067108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060651508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102378608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z97831106627880 cprintz978905260302540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048521166?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048521166423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048521166/original  a978-3-11-060651-5  AUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066278-8  Amsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2002d2015  a978-3-11-070067-1  AUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-102378-6  Amsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK